    <title>Flathunt User Guide</title>
    <para>
        <projectname>Flathunt</projectname> is an application that is used to teach you
        programming, along with another application named <projectname>Touch</projectname> [<link
            url="references.html">rk05</link>]. <projectname>Flathunt</projectname> is a "Scotland
        Yard"-like game that will mainly appear in the assignments for the Introduction to
        Programming course. It is based on <libraryname>TRAFFIC</libraryname> [<link
            url="references.html">sa05</link>] for modeling the city where the game takes place and
        on <libraryname>EiffelMedia</libraryname> (formerly known as <libraryname>ESDL</libraryname>
            [<link url="references.html">tgb03</link>]) for visualization. </para>
